lets add  this process to the init by including it as a script

Sure! To add the launchd process for the Hammerspoon daemon to your init script, you can add the following lines to the end of your script:

bash
Copy code
# Load the Hammerspoon daemon using launchd
launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.yourusername.hammerspoon.plist
Replace yourusername with your Mac username.

This code loads the Hammerspoon daemon using launchd when your init script is run. The daemon will automatically start up and run your Hammerspoon configuration when you log in to your Mac.

If you want to stop the daemon, you can run the following command:

javascript
Copy code
launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.yourusername.hammerspoon.plist
This command unloads the Hammerspoon daemon and stops running your Hammerspoon configuration.



